1
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:06,320
There's no time left.

2
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:08,080
They found me.

3
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:09,479
I can't leave.

4
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:14,120
Which will come first, tomorrow or an accident?

5
00:02:14,840 --> 00:02:15,760
They found me.

6
00:02:15,760 --> 00:02:17,600
You don't seem very happy.

7
00:02:21,720 --> 00:02:24,200
It's pathetic to be colleagues with someone like you.

8
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:25,560
No secrets at all.

9
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:28,560
Is it because of the anonymous message about

10
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:30,079
Xu Qiaoyue's MO?

11
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:34,720
There are no clues so far.

12
00:02:36,079 --> 00:02:37,810
I knew it wouldn't be that easy.

13
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:45,760
Many things in this world

14
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:48,640
are not as bad as you think.

15
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:51,880
Don't be so pessimistic.

16
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:53,280
The truth

17
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:54,520
never lies.

18
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:01,720
I hope it's really like you said.

19
00:03:02,640 --> 00:03:03,280
Thank you.

20
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:05,290
You actually say thank you?

21
00:03:06,480 --> 00:03:07,720
Do you think

22
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:09,780
I don't even have this basic manners?

23
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:12,850
That's not what I meant.

24
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:16,920
I'm just

25
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:18,610
not good with words.

26
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:21,320
Alright, don't say anything.

27
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:23,880
Drink up.

28
00:03:26,920 --> 00:03:28,760
But I can't drink.

29
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:29,880
You can't drink?

30
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:31,740
Why are you holding a bottle then?

31
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,400
Anyway,

32
00:03:57,880 --> 00:04:00,610
since we set up the Accident Investigation Team,

33
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:02,920
everything has gone smoothly.

34
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:07,080
I hope we can soon find

35
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:08,760
the answers to the doubts

36
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:10,520
in our hearts.

37
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:16,800
Hello?

38
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:18,560
Hello?

39
00:04:24,760 --> 00:04:26,600
Drunk already?

40
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:41,530
An accident.

41
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:44,320
Sobered up.

42
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:46,760
Morning.

43
00:04:49,440 --> 00:04:50,960
These are all from the past year,

44
00:04:50,960 --> 00:04:52,960
all the accident cases I've solved.

45
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,840
They were actually all murders.

46
00:04:55,560 --> 00:04:58,240
I didn't expect you to be the first to find it out.

47
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:02,680
This is the electrical leakage case.

48
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:06,720
This is the fatal dentist allergy case.

49
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:07,800
I noticed.

50
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:10,040
They all share a common trait.

51
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:13,640
Someone deliberately planned and guided them.

52
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:17,520
They named their organization Lighthouse.

53
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:19,920
They're just a bunch of outlaws claiming to be righteous,

54
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:21,520
fighting evil with evil,

55
00:05:21,520 --> 00:05:24,120
and putting themselves above the law.

56
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:27,040
Have you been investigating Lighthouse

57
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:30,200
because they hurt someone close to you?

58
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:31,520
Like your sister?

59
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,920
You managed to deduce that?

60
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:35,960
No.

61
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:37,090
Bai Xiaolin told me.

62
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:40,840
I thought you were a genius.

63
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:43,000
That blabbermouth.

64
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:48,050
Can you tell me about it?

65
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:50,640
Maybe I can help you.

66
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:58,680
It all started a year ago.

67
00:06:21,080 --> 00:06:22,000
Sister.

68
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:23,360
Zhuang Qing.

69
00:06:27,440 --> 00:06:28,880
Instead of studying hard abroad,

70
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:30,640
why did you come back so suddenly?

71
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:32,000
Did something happen?

72
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:33,760
We have a holiday.

73
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:35,320
Why won't you even let me come home?

74
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:37,000
Am I not letting you come home?

75
00:06:37,159 --> 00:06:39,920
The point is, it's not holiday time at your school.

76
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:41,480
Your sister is a police officer.

77
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:43,159
Lying to me is useless.

78
00:06:43,520 --> 00:06:45,320
Tell the truth, what's going on?

79
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:47,320
Or else I'll throw you out.

80
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:50,200
Sister,

81
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:52,460
my school is closed for the anniversary.

82
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:54,200
Sister.

83
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:55,060
I'm hungry.

84
00:06:55,080 --> 00:06:56,940
I want to eat the noodles you cook.

85
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:00,600
I'll settle the score with you later.

86
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:01,360
Just wait.

87
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:17,770
Eat up, you little glutton.

88
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:23,080
Eat slowly.

89
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:24,560
You're like this every time.

90
00:07:24,560 --> 00:07:25,800
Wolfing down your food,

91
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:27,480
not like a little girl at all.

92
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:37,200
Eat slowly.

93
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,000
Zhuang Qing.

94
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:46,400
Zhuang Qing,

95
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:48,480
why are you crying?

96
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:49,680
I'm fine, Sister.

97
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:50,680
The noodles you made

98
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:52,010
are just too delicious.

99
00:07:54,520 --> 00:07:55,000
Eat up.

100
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:01,780
Chief Sang, I know.

101
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:02,360
Okay.

102
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:03,040
Sister.

103
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:05,320
Okay, I'll be right there, Chief Sang.

104
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:06,450
Okay, I understand.

105
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:08,480
You.

106
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:10,080
What am I going to do with you?

107
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:12,400
You even lied to me about the anniversary,

108
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:13,480
about having a holiday.

109
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:14,920
The principal has already told me.

110
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:17,080
You haven't been to school for a long time, have you?

111
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:18,160
If you still don't go,

112
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,000
you will be expelled.

113
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:20,480
Do you realize the severity of this?

114
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:21,010
Let's go.

115
00:08:21,280 --> 00:08:22,040
Sister,

116
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:23,800
what if I don't go to school anymore

117
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:24,440
and be a police officer

118
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:25,480
just like you?

119
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:26,840
Be a police officer like me?

120
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:27,640
You?

121
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:28,600
You haven't even graduated from college.

122
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:29,720
How can you be a police officer like me?

123
00:08:29,720 --> 00:08:30,560
Sister,

124
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:32,900
aren't you afraid you won't see me again?

125
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:35,280
Just to play around,

126
00:08:35,280 --> 00:08:36,960
you actually made up such a thing.

127
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:38,640
You're really something.

128
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:41,360
Sister, if I marry a rich kid,

129
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:42,840
you will never see me again.

130
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:44,080
That would be great.

131
00:08:44,080 --> 00:08:45,410
I would finally be free.

132
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:47,600
I don't have that much time to see you off.

133
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:49,600
Hurry up and find your rich kid.

134
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:50,960
Sister,

135
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:52,640
I'll miss you.

136
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:57,240
You,

137
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:58,560
you're a big girl now.

138
00:08:58,560 --> 00:08:59,720
You can't be so playful anymore.

139
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:01,380
Why are you always so willful?

140
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:04,040
I promise you,

141
00:09:04,040 --> 00:09:06,440
I'll definitely visit you when I have time.

142
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:09,080
I don't have time to waste with you.

143
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:09,800
Just leave.

144
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:10,960
I didn't expect

145
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:12,850
that my decision at the time

146
00:09:12,880 --> 00:09:14,740
would end up hurting Zhuang Qing.

147
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:17,080
She didn't leave.

148
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:20,130
Instead, she went to the café we used to frequent.

149
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,880
This café

150
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:48,600
used to be Zhuang Qing's and my favorite place.

151
00:09:51,080 --> 00:09:54,240
It holds so many of our shared memories.

152
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:56,520
In my eyes,

153
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:58,680
she will always be that

154
00:09:58,920 --> 00:10:00,650
little girl who never grows up,

155
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:03,560
always waiting here for me to come back.

156
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:06,200
But ever since her accident,

157
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:08,320
I've never been back here.

158
00:10:09,880 --> 00:10:12,440
If only I had cared for her more in the past.

159
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:14,640
Or rather,

160
00:10:15,440 --> 00:10:17,440
if I hadn't driven her away that day,

161
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:20,000
would she have been fine?

162
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:22,880
Thinking back,

163
00:10:23,640 --> 00:10:24,880
her appearance,

164
00:10:24,880 --> 00:10:26,080
her actions,

165
00:10:26,440 --> 00:10:27,720
her emotions,

166
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:30,720
all seemed so abnormal.

167
00:10:32,160 --> 00:10:34,020
I should have noticed it earlier.

168
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:36,760
But until she died in front of me,

169
00:10:36,760 --> 00:10:38,920
I didn't realize it.

170
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:40,880
Perhaps,

171
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:44,240
she had already foreseen her own death.

172
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:50,040
So,

173
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:51,360
your current sadness

174
00:10:51,560 --> 00:10:52,840
comes more from

175
00:10:52,840 --> 00:10:53,800
guilt.

176
00:10:57,560 --> 00:10:58,960
Probably both.

177
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:03,240
So this case

178
00:11:03,760 --> 00:11:06,240
eventually went nowhere.

179
00:11:08,040 --> 00:11:09,600
There was no case at all.

180
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:11,240
After the accident,

181
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:13,120
the driver already said

182
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:15,400
that it was his negligence that day

183
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:17,200
that led to Zhuang Qing's death.

184
00:11:17,520 --> 00:11:18,680
But I really don't believe it.

185
00:11:18,680 --> 00:11:20,210
I can't accept this result.

186
00:11:21,880 --> 00:11:23,880
But I investigated for a long time,

187
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:26,340
and ultimately, all the evidence pointed to

188
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:29,400
this being an accident.

189
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:32,000
But you kept investigating,

190
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:33,400
and even

191
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:35,040
set up a department.

192
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:43,320
Because of this.

193
00:11:44,880 --> 00:11:47,320
This was left behind when Zhuang Qing died.

194
00:11:47,560 --> 00:11:48,560
Maybe

195
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:51,380
she wanted to leave some information for me.

196
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:02,960
There is no time.

197
00:12:03,280 --> 00:12:04,760
They have found me.

198
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:06,640
I can't leave.

199
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:09,040
Between an accident and tomorrow,

200
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:10,720
which will come first?

201
00:12:11,280 --> 00:12:12,010
Understood.

202
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,930
I understand all your intentions.

203
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:16,040
You suspect

204
00:12:16,120 --> 00:12:17,180
that this accident

205
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:19,160
was designed by the lighthouse,

206
00:12:19,160 --> 00:12:19,840
right?

207
00:12:23,880 --> 00:12:26,480
Although there is no direct proof in this case,

208
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:28,000
But judging from Zhuang Qing's

209
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:30,320
abnormal behavior at that time,

210
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:33,660
this was definitely no accident.

211
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:36,300
It must be related to the Lighthouse.

212
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:41,840
If they remain at large,

213
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:45,480
there will be more victims like Xu Qiaoyue

214
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:48,440
who become tools for them to escape the law

215
00:12:48,440 --> 00:12:50,800
and carry out criminal plans.

216
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:52,440
As a police officer,

217
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:55,170
I will never allow such an organization to exist.

218
00:12:55,560 --> 00:12:57,440
So I must keep investigating.

219
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:00,600
I will set up the Accident Investigation Team.

220
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:27,240
Mr. Li.

221
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:30,480
Your room expires tomorrow.

222
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:32,360
The manager asked me to check

223
00:13:32,360 --> 00:13:33,640
if you'd like to renew.

224
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:37,760
Mr. Li?

225
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:48,680
What's that smell?

226
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:56,440
Mr. Li, I'm coming in.

227
00:13:59,280 --> 00:14:00,240
Mr. Li?

228
00:14:10,320 --> 00:14:11,680
Someone's dead!
